        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=Python is prone to various security vulnerabilities in bundled
  expat.|insight=The following vulnerabilities exist:

  - CVE-2016-0718: Expat allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) or
  possibly execute arbitrary code via a malformed input document, which triggers a buffer overflow.

  - CVE-2016-4472: The overflow protection in Expat is removed by compilers with certain optimization
  settings, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) or possibly execute
  arbitrary code via crafted XML data.

  NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2015-1283 and CVE-2015-2716.|affected=Python prior to version 2.7.14, versions 3.3.x prior to 3.3.7,
  3.4.x prior to 3.4.7, 3.5.x prior to 3.5.3 and 3.6.x prior to 3.6.2.|impact=|solution=Update to version 2.7.14, 3.3.7, 3.4.7, 3.5.4, 3.6.2 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
