  exists, which may lead to remote code execution in certain Python applications that accept
  floating-point numbers as untrusted input, as demonstrated by a '1e300' argument to
  'c_double.from_param'. This occurs because sprintf is used unsafely.|affected=Python prior to version 3.6.13, versions 3.7.x prior to
  3.7.10, 3.8.x prior to 3.8.8 and 3.9.x prior to 3.9.2.|impact=|solution=Update to version 3.6.13, 3.7.10, 3.8.8, 3.9.2 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
