      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.125558">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>Python DoS Vulnerability (Dec 2025) - Linux</name>
        <family>Denial of Service</family>
        <cvss_base>9.1</cvss_base>
        <severities score="9.1">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v3">
            <origin>NVD</origin>
            <date>2025-12-30T15:08:14Z</date>
            <score>9.1</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:H</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:H|summary=Python is prone to a denial of service (DoS) vulnerability.|insight=When reading an HTTP response from a server, if no read amount
  is specified, the default behavior will be to use Content-Length. This allows a malicious
  server to cause the client to read large amounts of data into memory, potentially causing
  out-of-memory (OOM) or other DoS conditions.|affected=Python prior to version 3.13.11 and 3.14.x prior to 3.14.1.

  Note: Fixes have been backported to maintenance branches (3.10, 3.12) but specific
  patch versions are not yet available.|impact=|solution=Update to version 3.14.1 or later, or to the latest
  maintenance release of your Python version series (3.10.x, 3.12.x) once patches
  are available. Please see the references for more information.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 3.14.1 or later, or to the latest
  maintenance release of your Python version series (3.10.x, 3.12.x) once patches
  are available. Please see the references for more information.</solution>
        <refs>
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2025-13836" />
          <ref type="url" id="https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/119451" />
