        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N|summary=Python is prone to a HTTP header injection vulnerability
  (follow-up of CVE-2016-5699).|insight=The following vulnerabilities exist:

  - CVE-2019-9740: An issue was discovered in urllib2 in Python 2.x and urllib in Python 3.x.
  CRLF injection is possible if the attacker controls a url parameter, as demonstrated by the first
  argument to 'urllib.request.urlopen' with 'rn' (specifically in the query string after a '?'
  character) followed by an HTTP header or a Redis command.

  - CVE-2019-9947: An issue was discovered in urllib2 in Python 2.x and urllib in Python 3.x.
  CRLF injection is possible if the attacker controls a url parameter, as demonstrated by the first
  argument to 'urllib.request.urlopen' with 'rn' (specifically in the path component of a URL that
  lacks a '?' character) followed by an HTTP header or a Redis command.|affected=Python versions 2.x prior to 2.7.17, 3.x prior to 3.5.8, 3.6.x
  prior to 3.6.9 and 3.7.x prior to 3.7.4.|impact=|solution=The vendor has released updates. Please see the references for
  more information.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
