        <tags>cvss_base_vector=AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:N/I:N/A:P|summary=Python is prone to a vulnerability in the ssl module.|insight=A defect was discovered in the Python 'ssl' module where there
  is a memory race condition with the ssl.SSLContext methods 'cert_store_stats()' and
  'get_ca_certs()'. The race condition can be triggered if the methods are called at the same time
  as certificates are loaded into the SSLContext, such as during the TLS handshake with a
  certificate directory configured.|affected=Python prior to version 3.8.20, 3.9.x prior to 3.9.20, 3.10.x
  prior to 3.10.14, 3.11.x prior to 3.11.9 and 3.12.x prior to 3.12.3.|impact=|solution=Update to version 3.8.20, 3.9.20, 3.10.14, 3.11.9, 3.12.3
  or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 3.8.20, 3.9.20, 3.10.14, 3.11.9, 3.12.3
  or later.</solution>
