      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.114744">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>Python Buffer Over-Read Vulnerability (Jul 2024) - Linux</name>
        <family>General</family>
        <cvss_base>5.0</cvss_base>
        <severities score="5.0">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v2">
            <origin />
            <date>2024-08-13T08:37:31Z</date>
            <score>5.0</score>
            <value>AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N|summary=Python is prone to a buffer over-read vulnerability in
  SSLContext.set_npn_protocols().|insight=The product doesn't disallow configuring an empty list ('[]')
  for SSLContext.set_npn_protocols() which is an invalid value for the underlying OpenSSL API. This
  results in a buffer over-read when NPN is used (see CVE-2024-5535 for OpenSSL). This vulnerability
  is of low severity due to NPN being not widely used and specifying an empty list likely being
  uncommon in-practice (typically a protocol name would be configured).|affected=Python versions prior to 3.10.|impact=|solution=Suggested mitigation by the vendor is one of the following:

  - Update to Python 3.10 or later where NPN isn't supported

  - Avoid using NPN via SSLContext.set_npn_protocols()

  - Avoid providing an empty list as a parameter to SSLContext.set_npn_protocols()|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Suggested mitigation by the vendor is one of the following:

  - Update to Python 3.10 or later where NPN isn't supported

  - Avoid using NPN via SSLContext.set_npn_protocols()

  - Avoid providing an empty list as a parameter to SSLContext.set_npn_protocols()</solution>
        <refs>
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2024-5642" />
