        <tags>cvss_base_vector=AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:N/A:N|summary=Python is prone to a vulnerability in the ipaddress module.|insight=The 'ipaddress' module contained incorrect information about
  whether certain IPv4 and IPv6 addresses were designated as 'globally reachable' or 'private'.
  This affected the 'is_private' and 'is_global' properties of the ipaddress.IPv4Address,
  ipaddress.IPv4Network, ipaddress.IPv6Address, and ipaddress.IPv6Network classes, where values
  wouldn't be returned in accordance with the latest information from the IANA Special-Purpose
  Address Registries.|affected=Python prior to version 3.8.20, 3.9.x prior to 3.9.20, 3.10.x
  prior to 3.10.15, 3.11.x prior to 3.11.10 and 3.12.x prior to 3.12.4.|impact=|solution=Update to version 3.8.20, 3.9.20, 3.10.15, 3.11.10, 3.12.4 or
  later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 3.8.20, 3.9.20, 3.10.15, 3.11.10, 3.12.4 or
  later.</solution>
