  hash collisions predictably and makes it easier for context-dependent attackers to cause a denial
  of service (CPU consumption) via crafted input to an application that maintains a hash table.|affected=Python 2.7 before 3.4.|impact=|solution=The vendor has released updates. Please see the references for
  more information.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
